children.subject: Try again. It seems I missed a checkbox and although the new section was open for enrollment, it wasn't displayed so no one could sign up for it. That problem should be fixed now.

Because there are still not enough section spots to accommodate the lecture spots, I am still on the wait list (position 33). I haven't yet dropped myself and re-added because I'm pretty sure that will just put me at the bottom of the wait list again. 

Am I correct in that I should just sit tight for the moment, and then if a new section opens up to accommodate the rest of the lecture spots, I'll switch to that one?

history.content:
If you are currently wait listed for this class, you will need to drop & re-enroll to get in. The system will NOT automatically switch sections for you.

Be sure there are open seats in both the new section and the lecture before you do drop/re-enroll, otherwise you will get bumped to the bottom of the wait list.

And as has been stated elsewhere - we are not overriding time conflicts for summer EECS classes.
history.subject: Summer: CS 188 has added a new section, lecture capacity has been expanded
